<sec id="sec_B.2" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:tbx="urn:iso:std:iso:30042:ed-1"><label>B.2</label><title>Definitions for stability calculations</title><p>The following factors and symbols shall be used to calculate the stability:</p><array id="tab_f"><table width="651"><col width="5.77%"/><col width="94.23%"/><tbody><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top"><italic>G</italic><sub>t</sub></td><td align="justify" valign="top">is the total weight of the rig including all equipment;</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top">X<sub>t</sub></td><td align="justify" valign="top">is the abscissa of the total centre of gravity referred to the tipping line;</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top">Y<sub>t</sub></td><td align="justify" valign="top">is the ordinate of the total centre of gravity referred to the tipping line;</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top"><italic>α</italic><sub>s</sub></td><td align="justify" valign="top">is the static stability angle (α<sub>s</sub> = arctan X<sub>t</sub>/Y<sub>t</sub>);</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top"><italic>M</italic><sub>w</sub></td><td align="justify" valign="top">is the overturning moment of wind forces;</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top"><italic>M</italic><sub>a</sub></td><td align="justify" valign="top">is the overturning moment of centrifugal forces;</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top"><italic>M</italic><sub>f</sub></td><td align="justify" valign="top">is the overturning moment of other working forces;</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top"><italic>M</italic><sub>r</sub></td><td align="justify" valign="top">= <italic>M</italic><sub>w</sub> + <italic>M</italic><sub>a</sub> + <italic>M</italic><sub>f</sub>, i.e. is the total overturning moment;</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top"><italic>M</italic><sub>s</sub></td><td align="justify" valign="top">= <italic>G</italic><sub>t</sub><bold>∙</bold> X<sub>t</sub>, i.e. is the total stabilizing moment;</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top">∆<italic>x</italic></td><td align="justify" valign="top">= <italic>M</italic><sub>r</sub>/<italic>G</italic><sub>t</sub>, i.e.is  the apparent horizontal displacement of the centre of gravity, equivalent to the effect of the overturning moments;</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top"><italic>α</italic><sub>d</sub></td><td align="justify" valign="top">is the dynamic stability angle, i.e. <italic>α</italic><sub>d</sub> = arctan (X<sub>t</sub> - ∆<italic>x</italic>)Y<sub>t</sub>.</td></tr></tbody></table></array><p>Tipping lines are defined in <std id="id-0bdf8edd-25c2-46ee-be5e-3fe5cab9e910"><std-ref>ISO 18758-1</std-ref></std> and also shown in <xref as:rid="chunks/86182/sec_B.2#fig_B.2" ref-type="fig" id="fig_B.2">Figures B.2</xref> to <xref as:rid="chunks/86182/sec_B.2#fig_B.6" ref-type="fig" id="fig_B.6">B.6</xref>. The stability angles are illustrated in <xref as:rid="chunks/86182/sec_B.2#fig_B.6" ref-type="fig" id="fig_B.6">Figure B.6</xref>.</p><fig fig-type="figure" id="fig_B.1"><label>Figure B.1</label><caption><title>Wheel-mounted rig</title></caption><graphic xlink:href="fig_B.1"><?isoimg-id 18758-2_ed1figB1.EPS?></graphic><table-wrap content-type="fig-index" id="tab_g" position="float"><caption><title>Key</title></caption><table width="652"><col width="4.08%"/><col width="95.92%"/><tbody><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top">1</td><td align="justify" valign="top">jack support points</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top">2</td><td align="justify" valign="top">wheel support points</td></tr></tbody></table></table-wrap></fig><p/><p/><fig fig-type="figure" id="fig_B.2"><label>Figure B.2</label><caption><title>Tipping lines for wheel-mounted carrier when tramming</title></caption><graphic xlink:href="fig_B.2"><?isoimg-id 18758-2_ed1figB2.EPS?></graphic></fig><fig fig-type="figure" id="fig_B.3"><label>Figure B.3</label><caption><title>Crawler-mounted rig</title></caption><graphic xlink:href="fig_B.3"><?isoimg-id 18758-2_ed1figB3.EPS?></graphic><table-wrap content-type="fig-index" id="tab_h" position="float"><caption><title>Key</title></caption><table width="652"><col width="4.08%"/><col width="95.92%"/><tbody><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top">1</td><td align="justify" valign="top">tipping lines, see <xref as:rid="chunks/86182/sec_B.2#fig_B.6" ref-type="fig" id="fig_B.6">Figure B.6</xref></td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top">2</td><td align="justify" valign="top">possible support point</td></tr></tbody></table></table-wrap></fig><p/><p/><p/><fig fig-type="figure" id="fig_B.4"><label>Figure B.4</label><caption><title>A pair of support points form a tipping line</title></caption><graphic xlink:href="fig_B.4"><?isoimg-id 18758-2_ed1figB4.EPS?></graphic></fig><?Para Page_Break?><p/><p/><p/><fig fig-type="figure" id="fig_B.5"><label>Figure B.5</label><caption><title>Tipping lines of crawlers</title></caption><graphic xlink:href="fig_B.5.0"><label>a)</label><caption><title>Tipping line in direction of travel</title></caption><?isoimg-id 18758-2_ed1figB5a.EPS?></graphic><graphic xlink:href="fig_B.5.1"><label>b)</label><caption><title>Tipping line perpendicular to the direction of travel</title></caption><?isoimg-id 18758-2_ed1figB5b.EPS?></graphic><table-wrap content-type="fig-index" id="tab_i" position="float"><caption><title>Key</title></caption><table width="644"><col width="4.13%"/><col width="48.82%"/><col width="3.7%"/><col width="43.35%"/><tbody><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top">1</td><td align="justify" valign="top">choose 1 if beta is lower than or equal to 2 degrees</td><td align="justify" valign="top">6</td><td align="justify" valign="top">chain link</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top">2</td><td align="justify" valign="top">choose 2 if beta is greater than 2 degrees</td><td align="justify" valign="top">7</td><td align="justify" valign="top">outward direction</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top">3</td><td align="justify" valign="top">roller</td><td align="justify" valign="top">a</td><td align="justify" valign="top">Chain type track.</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top">4</td><td align="justify" valign="top">drive or idler</td><td align="justify" valign="top">b</td><td align="justify" valign="top">Shoe type track.</td></tr><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top">5</td><td align="justify" valign="top">shoe</td><td align="left" valign="top"/><td align="left" valign="top"/></tr></tbody></table></table-wrap></fig><fig fig-type="figure" id="fig_B.6"><label>Figure B.6</label><caption><title>Stability angle</title></caption><graphic xlink:href="fig_B.6"><?isoimg-id 18758-2_ed1figB6.EPS?></graphic><table-wrap content-type="fig-index" id="tab_j" position="float"><caption><title>Key</title></caption><table width="652"><col width="4.08%"/><col width="95.92%"/><tbody><tr><td align="justify" scope="row" valign="top">1</td><td align="justify" valign="top">tipping line</td></tr></tbody></table></table-wrap></fig></sec>
